{"id": "1520798056084410428", "channel_id": "1520725723160121424", "author_id": "845527584157597716", "author_name": "lurenjiao", "content": "It's specifically about Pontos. Based on the current test results, fixed damage no longer directly triggers the Wheel's 15% effect. This means Pontos can stack a large amount of Critical Damage and then trigger the Wheel using direct damage instead.\n\nYou can calculate the numbers yourself under different scenarios. The differences in damage are clear, and it's a very straightforward nerf.", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T14:28:31.632000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1520725723160121424", "mentions": ["1437487264023318668"], "reply_to": "1520797548653314169"}
{"id": "1520798459190448139", "channel_id": "1520725723160121424", "author_id": "845527584157597716", "author_name": "lurenjiao", "content": "His derived cards can increase his own Critical Damage by up to 45% when they reach their full effect. He has three of these cards, and since they deal fixed damage, they can stack that Critical Damage first and then use other sources of direct damage to trigger the Wheel.\n\nDo you really think that adding 5% base Critical Damage is enough to make up for that loss?", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T14:30:07.740000+00:00", "thread_id": "1520725723160121424"}
{"id": "1520798481856594001", "channel_id": "1520725723160121424", "author_id": "845527584157597716", "author_name": "lurenjiao", "content": "<@1437487264023318668>", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T14:30:13.144000+00:00", "thread_id": "1520725723160121424", "mentions": ["1437487264023318668"]}
{"id": "1520799012238921841", "channel_id": "1520725723160121424", "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "content": "What I'm saying is not that the change on the wheel is good. \nI'm just saying that affirming that Pontos is straight up a worthless unit and should be reworked before is even out is a bit of an extreme statement.", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T14:32:19.597000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1520725723160121424", "edited_timestamp": "2026-06-28T14:32:24.543000+00:00", "mentions": ["845527584157597716"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "reply_to": "1520798459190448139"}
